answers.body_markdown:
if you want to use dynamic addressing
in linux based system :

    String filePath = System.getProperty(&quot;user.dir&quot;)+&quot;/path/to/file/QR_Code.png&quot;;

in windows based system :

    String filePath = System.getProperty(&quot;user.dir&quot;)+&quot;\\path\\to\\file\\QR_Code.png&quot;;

System.getProperty(&quot;user.dir&quot;) is your project address.

if you want to use static addressing
in linux based system :

    String filePath = &quot;/home/username/eclipse-workspace/test/path/to/file/QR_Code.png&quot;;

in windows based system :

    String filePath = &quot;C:\\Work\\QR_CODE\\QR_Code.png&quot;;

